Nyandarua had eight cases followed by Laikipia, Kitui, Kakamega each six, Taita Taveta, Turkana, Mandera and Bungoma each four, Murang’a and Nyamira each three, Baringo, Elgeyo Marakwet, Kwale and Makueni each two, and Isiolo, Kericho, Kirinyaga, Kisumu and Nandi each one. The county is struggling to cope with the rising number of Covid-19 patients seeking treatment in public and private hospitals. The number of confirmed infections since last March has increased by 1,184 to 138,077. What does Mr Kenyatta want to do with the immense powers he’s consolidating? Court says concept of succession is about generational transfer of wealth from parents to their children.